strings : stutter

Write a method named stutter that accepts a string parameter returns a new string replacing each of its characters with two consecutive copies of that character.
For example, a call of stutter("hello") would return "hheelllloo".

 public static String stutter(String str) {
        String stutteredString = "";
        int stutterCount = 2;
        for(int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < stutterCount; j++) {
                stutteredString += str.charAt(i);
            }
        }
        return stutteredString;
    }



